{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":954,"text":"I'm here today to talk about\nthe two ideas that,"},{"time":3904,"text":"at least based on\nmy observations at Khan Academy,"},{"time":6286,"text":"are kind of the core,\nor the key leverage points for learning."},{"time":10188,"text":"And it's the idea of mastery"},{"time":12228,"text":"and the idea of mindset."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14037,"text":"I saw this in the early days\nworking with my cousins."},{"time":16895,"text":"A lot of them were having trouble\nwith math at first,"},{"time":19399,"text":"because they had all of these gaps\naccumulated in their learning."},{"time":22477,"text":"And because of that, at some point\nthey got to an algebra class"},{"time":25490,"text":"and they might have been a little bit\nshaky on some of the pre-algebra,"},{"time":28916,"text":"and because of that, they thought\nthey didn't have the math gene."},{"time":32385,"text":"Or they'd get to a calculus class,"},{"time":34072,"text":"and they'd be a little bit\nshaky on the algebra."},{"time":36858,"text":"I saw it in the early days"},{"time":38452,"text":"when I was uploading\nsome of those videos on YouTube,"},{"time":42004,"text":"and I realized that people\nwho were not my cousins were watching."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45305,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":47194,"text":"And at first, those comments\nwere just simple thank-yous."},{"time":51084,"text":"I thought that was a pretty big deal."},{"time":53077,"text":"I don't know how much time\nyou all spend on YouTube."},{"time":55553,"text":"Most of the comments are not \"Thank you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":57664,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":59145,"text":"They're a little edgier than that."},{"time":60807,"text":"But then the comments\ngot a little more intense,"},{"time":63262,"text":"student after student saying\nthat they had grown up not liking math."},{"time":67742,"text":"It was getting difficult as they got\ninto more advanced math topics."},{"time":70965,"text":"By the time they got to algebra,"},{"time":72517,"text":"they had so many gaps in their knowledge\nthey couldn't engage with it."},{"time":75869,"text":"They thought they didn't\nhave the math gene."},{"time":77966,"text":"But when they were a bit older,"},{"time":79470,"text":"they took a little agency\nand decided to engage."},{"time":81737,"text":"They found resources like Khan Academy"},{"time":83613,"text":"and they were able to fill in those gaps\nand master those concepts,"},{"time":86787,"text":"and that reinforced their mindset\nthat it wasn't fixed;"},{"time":89401,"text":"that they actually were capable\nof learning mathematics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92990,"text":"And in a lot of ways, this is how\nyou would master a lot of things in life."},{"time":97067,"text":"It's the way you would\nlearn a martial art."},{"time":99390,"text":"In a martial art, you would\npractice the white belt skills"},{"time":102580,"text":"as long as necessary,"},{"time":104017,"text":"and only when you've mastered it"},{"time":105592,"text":"you would move on to become a yellow belt."},{"time":107751,"text":"It's the way you learn\na musical instrument:"},{"time":109846,"text":"you practice the basic piece\nover and over again,"},{"time":112164,"text":"and only when you've mastered it,"},{"time":113776,"text":"you go on to the more advanced one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":115471,"text":"But what we point out --"},{"time":116835,"text":"this is not the way a traditional\nacademic model is structured,"},{"time":121344,"text":"the type of academic model\nthat most of us grew up in."},{"time":124703,"text":"In a traditional academic model,"},{"time":126269,"text":"we group students together,\nusually by age,"},{"time":128712,"text":"and around middle school,"},{"time":130015,"text":"by age and perceived ability,"},{"time":131885,"text":"and we shepherd them all\ntogether at the same pace."},{"time":135038,"text":"And what typically happens,"},{"time":136359,"text":"let's say we're in a middle school\npre-algebra class,"},{"time":138884,"text":"and the current unit is on exponents,"},{"time":140702,"text":"the teacher will give\na lecture on exponents,"},{"time":142916,"text":"then we'll go home, do some homework."},{"time":145225,"text":"The next morning,\nwe'll review the homework,"},{"time":147303,"text":"then another lecture, homework,\nlecture, homework."},{"time":149675,"text":"That will continue for about\ntwo or three weeks,"},{"time":151960,"text":"and then we get a test."},{"time":153159,"text":"On that test, maybe I get a 75 percent,"},{"time":156501,"text":"maybe you get a 90 percent,"},{"time":157942,"text":"maybe you get a 95 percent."},{"time":159950,"text":"And even though the test identified\ngaps in our knowledge,"},{"time":162721,"text":"I didn't know 25 percent of the material."},{"time":164704,"text":"Even the A student, what was\nthe five percent they didn't know?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":167700,"text":"Even though we've identified the gaps,"},{"time":169537,"text":"the whole class will then\nmove on to the next subject,"},{"time":172099,"text":"probably a more advanced subject\nthat's going to build on those gaps."},{"time":175525,"text":"It might be logarithms\nor negative exponents."},{"time":178922,"text":"And that process continues,\nand you immediately start to realize"},{"time":181977,"text":"how strange this is."},{"time":183176,"text":"I didn't know 25 percent\nof the more foundational thing,"},{"time":185971,"text":"and now I'm being pushed\nto the more advanced thing."},{"time":188440,"text":"And this will continue for months, years,\nall the way until at some point,"},{"time":192176,"text":"I might be in an algebra class\nor trigonometry class"},{"time":194640,"text":"and I hit a wall."},{"time":195921,"text":"And it's not because algebra\nis fundamentally difficult"},{"time":198599,"text":"or because the student isn't bright."},{"time":202615,"text":"It's because I'm seeing an equation\nand they're dealing with exponents"},{"time":205950,"text":"and that 30 percent\nthat I didn't know is showing up."},{"time":208703,"text":"And then I start to disengage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212469,"text":"To appreciate how absurd that is,"},{"time":215919,"text":"imagine if we did other things\nin our life that way."},{"time":219124,"text":"Say, home-building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220602,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":224878,"text":"So we bring in the contractor and say,"},{"time":228296,"text":"\"We were told we have\ntwo weeks to build a foundation."},{"time":230868,"text":"Do what you can.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":232228,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":234985,"text":"So they do what they can."},{"time":236801,"text":"Maybe it rains."},{"time":237981,"text":"Maybe some of the supplies don't show up."},{"time":239974,"text":"And two weeks later,\nthe inspector comes, looks around,"},{"time":243308,"text":"says, \"OK, the concrete\nis still wet right over there,"},{"time":245997,"text":"that part's not quite up to code ..."},{"time":248838,"text":"I'll give it an 80 percent.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":250220,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":251308,"text":"You say, \"Great! That's a C.\nLet's build the first floor.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":254067,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":255109,"text":"Same thing."},{"time":256287,"text":"We have two weeks, do what you can,\ninspector shows up, it's a 75 percent."},{"time":260150,"text":"Great, that's a D-plus."},{"time":261333,"text":"Second floor, third floor,"},{"time":262603,"text":"and all of a sudden,\nwhile you're building the third floor,"},{"time":265405,"text":"the whole structure collapses."},{"time":266865,"text":"And if your reaction is the reaction\nyou typically have in education,"},{"time":270133,"text":"or that a lot of folks have,"},{"time":271498,"text":"you might say, maybe\nwe had a bad contractor,"},{"time":273628,"text":"or maybe we needed better inspection\nor more frequent inspection."},{"time":276745,"text":"But what was really broken\nwas the process."},{"time":279018,"text":"We were artificially constraining\nhow long we had to something,"},{"time":282071,"text":"pretty much ensuring a variable outcome,"},{"time":284468,"text":"and we took the trouble of inspecting\nand identifying those gaps,"},{"time":288016,"text":"but then we built right on top of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289973,"text":"So the idea of mastery learning\nis to do the exact opposite."},{"time":292934,"text":"Instead of artificially\nconstraining, fixing"},{"time":295426,"text":"when and how long you work on something,"},{"time":297438,"text":"pretty much ensuring\nthat variable outcome,"},{"time":299680,"text":"the A, B, C, D, F --"},{"time":301980,"text":"do it the other way around."},{"time":303844,"text":"What's variable is when and how long"},{"time":305660,"text":"a student actually has\nto work on something,"},{"time":307778,"text":"and what's fixed is that\nthey actually master the material."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311445,"text":"And it's important to realize"},{"time":313120,"text":"that not only will this make the student\nlearn their exponents better,"},{"time":316509,"text":"but it'll reinforce\nthe right mindset muscles."},{"time":319491,"text":"It makes them realize that if you got\n20 percent wrong on something,"},{"time":322943,"text":"it doesn't mean that you have\na C branded in your DNA somehow."},{"time":326356,"text":"It means that you should just\nkeep working on it."},{"time":328814,"text":"You should have grit;\nyou should have perseverance;"},{"time":331330,"text":"you should take agency over your learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333908,"text":"Now, a lot of skeptics might say,\nwell, hey, this is all great,"},{"time":336922,"text":"philosophically, this whole idea\nof mastery-based learning"},{"time":339667,"text":"and its connection to mindset,"},{"time":341127,"text":"students taking agency\nover their learning."},{"time":343250,"text":"It makes a lot of sense,\nbut it seems impractical."},{"time":346409,"text":"To actually do it, every student\nwould be on their own track."},{"time":349830,"text":"It would have to be personalized,"},{"time":351478,"text":"you'd have to have private tutors\nand worksheets for every student."},{"time":354684,"text":"And these aren't new ideas --"},{"time":356207,"text":"there were experiments\nin Winnetka, Illinois, 100 years ago,"},{"time":359057,"text":"where they did mastery-based learning\nand saw great results,"},{"time":361899,"text":"but they said it wouldn't scale\nbecause it was logistically difficult."},{"time":365220,"text":"The teacher had to give different\nworksheets to every student,"},{"time":368151,"text":"give on-demand assessments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369463,"text":"But now today, it's no longer impractical."},{"time":371748,"text":"We have the tools to do it."},{"time":373138,"text":"Students see an explanation\nat their own time and pace?"},{"time":375757,"text":"There's on-demand video for that."},{"time":377376,"text":"They need practice? They need feedback?"},{"time":379472,"text":"There's adaptive exercises\nreadily available for students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384311,"text":"And when that happens,\nall sorts of neat things happen."},{"time":386929,"text":"One, the students can actually\nmaster the concepts,"},{"time":389726,"text":"but they're also building\ntheir growth mindset,"},{"time":391945,"text":"they're building grit, perseverance,"},{"time":393766,"text":"they're taking agency over their learning."},{"time":395813,"text":"And all sorts of beautiful things\ncan start to happen"},{"time":398394,"text":"in the actual classroom."},{"time":400054,"text":"Instead of it being focused\non the lecture,"},{"time":402136,"text":"students can interact with each other."},{"time":403978,"text":"They can get deeper mastery\nover the material."},{"time":406160,"text":"They can go into simulations,\nSocratic dialogue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408537,"text":"To appreciate what we're talking about"},{"time":411240,"text":"and the tragedy of lost potential here,"},{"time":415311,"text":"I'd like to give a little bit\nof a thought experiment."},{"time":418985,"text":"If we were to go 400 years\ninto the past to Western Europe,"},{"time":424075,"text":"which even then, was one of the more\nliterate parts of the planet,"},{"time":427263,"text":"you would see that about 15 percent\nof the population knew how to read."},{"time":431556,"text":"And I suspect that if you asked someone\nwho did know how to read,"},{"time":435218,"text":"say a member of the clergy,"},{"time":437138,"text":"\"What percentage of the population\ndo you think is even capable of reading?\""},{"time":440774,"text":"They might say, \"Well,\nwith a great education system,"},{"time":444359,"text":"maybe 20 or 30 percent.\""},{"time":447424,"text":"But if you fast forward to today,"},{"time":449035,"text":"we know that that prediction\nwould have been wildly pessimistic,"},{"time":452074,"text":"that pretty close to 100 percent\nof the population is capable of reading."},{"time":456223,"text":"But if I were to ask you\na similar question:"},{"time":459494,"text":"\"What percentage of the population\ndo you think is capable"},{"time":463057,"text":"of truly mastering calculus,"},{"time":465954,"text":"or understanding organic chemistry,"},{"time":468991,"text":"or being able to contribute\nto cancer research?\""},{"time":472301,"text":"A lot of you might say, \"Well,\nwith a great education system,"},{"time":475222,"text":"maybe 20, 30 percent.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":477778,"text":"But what if that estimate"},{"time":479115,"text":"is just based on your own experience\nin a non-mastery framework,"},{"time":482526,"text":"your own experience with yourself\nor observing your peers,"},{"time":485382,"text":"where you're being pushed\nat this set pace through classes,"},{"time":488195,"text":"accumulating all these gaps?"},{"time":489558,"text":"Even when you got that 95 percent,"},{"time":491223,"text":"what was that five percent you missed?"},{"time":493059,"text":"And it keeps accumulating --\nyou get to an advanced class,"},{"time":495810,"text":"all of a sudden you hit a wall and say,"},{"time":497706,"text":"\"I'm not meant to be a cancer researcher;"},{"time":499733,"text":"not meant to be a physicist;\nnot meant to be a mathematician.\""},{"time":502685,"text":"I suspect that that actually is the case,"},{"time":504686,"text":"but if you were allowed to be operating\nin a mastery framework,"},{"time":508536,"text":"if you were allowed to really\ntake agency over your learning,"},{"time":511977,"text":"and when you get something wrong,"},{"time":513597,"text":"embrace it -- view that failure\nas a moment of learning --"},{"time":516413,"text":"that number, the percent\nthat could really master calculus"},{"time":520394,"text":"or understand organic chemistry,"},{"time":522178,"text":"is actually a lot closer to 100 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525601,"text":"And this isn't even just a \"nice to have.\""},{"time":529019,"text":"I think it's a social imperative."},{"time":531511,"text":"We're exiting what you could call\nthe industrial age"},{"time":535386,"text":"and we're going into\nthis information revolution."},{"time":539646,"text":"And it's clear that some\nthings are happening."},{"time":541844,"text":"In the industrial age,\nsociety was a pyramid."},{"time":543981,"text":"At the base of the pyramid,\nyou needed human labor."},{"time":549085,"text":"In the middle of the pyramid,\nyou had an information processing,"},{"time":552442,"text":"a bureaucracy class,"},{"time":554064,"text":"and at the top of the pyramid,\nyou had your owners of capital"},{"time":557762,"text":"and your entrepreneurs"},{"time":559785,"text":"and your creative class."},{"time":561904,"text":"But we know what's happening already,"},{"time":563724,"text":"as we go into this information revolution."},{"time":565763,"text":"The bottom of that pyramid,\nautomation, is going to take over."},{"time":568740,"text":"Even that middle tier,\ninformation processing,"},{"time":571089,"text":"that's what computers are good at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572739,"text":"So as a society, we have a question:"},{"time":574510,"text":"All this new productivity is happening\nbecause of this technology,"},{"time":577652,"text":"but who participates in it?"},{"time":579006,"text":"Is it just going to be that very top\nof the pyramid, in which case,"},{"time":582225,"text":"what does everyone else do?"},{"time":583590,"text":"How do they operate?"},{"time":584780,"text":"Or do we do something\nthat's more aspirational?"},{"time":587581,"text":"Do we actually attempt\nto invert the pyramid,"},{"time":590715,"text":"where you have a large creative class,"},{"time":592740,"text":"where almost everyone\ncan participate as an entrepreneur,"},{"time":596445,"text":"an artist, as a researcher?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":598850,"text":"And I don't think that this is utopian."},{"time":600804,"text":"I really think that this\nis all based on the idea"},{"time":603192,"text":"that if we let people\ntap into their potential"},{"time":605400,"text":"by mastering concepts,"},{"time":607388,"text":"by being able to exercise agency\nover their learning,"},{"time":610989,"text":"that they can get there."},{"time":612672,"text":"And when you think of it\nas just a citizen of the world,"},{"time":616696,"text":"it's pretty exciting."},{"time":617983,"text":"I mean, think about\nthe type of equity we can we have,"},{"time":620635,"text":"and the rate at which civilization\ncould even progress."},{"time":624339,"text":"And so, I'm pretty optimistic about it."},{"time":626576,"text":"I think it's going to be\na pretty exciting time to be alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630163,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631353,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}